      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Unions are not a lost cause, but their effectiveness has fundamentally shifted from direct wage bargaining to political influence and collective action. While they have successfully halted the privatization of essential infrastructure and protected workers from predatory wage cuts in the gig economy, their ability to stop corporate consolidation is severely limited by the sheer scale of modern conglomerates. The real power today lies in their ability to mobilize voters and pressure corporations through litigation and public campaigns, rather than just signing contracts.",
